There is an ongoing debate about whether dry chicken wings are better than wet ones, and while there are sound arguments on both sides, we can all agree that in all forms, they are delicious. For a chicken wing, the most important thing is the marinade and sauce, and this Captain Morgan glaze is a must try. The simple dish just needs a few recipes, making it incredibly affordable and tasty. Give it a try and let us know what you think. Ingredients: Marinade: 3 cups Captain Morgan rum Fresh lime juice (3-4 limes) 2 tbsp grated ginger 5 cloves grated garlic 2 scotch bonnet chilli chopped 1tbsp black pepper 2 tbsp oil 3 tbsp soy sauce 1 tbsp Garam masala 1 tbsp cumin Chicken wings. Method   